India Equity Movers: Areva T&D, Kingfisher Air, Suzlon Energy

-- B y   A m e y a   K a r v e
-- 
2011-03-15T04:30:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/india-equity-movers-areva-t-d-kingfisher-air-suzlon-energy.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  India  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 9:59 a.m. in Mumbai.  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, fell
416.59, or 2.3 percent, to 18,022.89, its steepest decline since
Feb. 24 as all 30 members declined.    Areva T&D India Ltd. (ATD)  : The local unit of the
world’s biggest supplier of nuclear services tumbled 4.5 percent
to 233.15 rupees, poised for its lowest close since May 2009, on
concern an accident at a Japanese reactor may curb demand for
atomic energy.    Kingfisher Airlines Ltd. (KAIR)   slid 4.3 percent to 39.9
rupees, the most since Feb. 24. The majority shareholders of the
nation’s second-biggest carrier pledged 55.5 percent of its
stock, according to a stock exchange filing.    Suzlon Energy Ltd. (SUEL)   fell 3.7 percent to 45.75
rupees, set for its lowest close in more than a month. India’s
largest wind-turbine maker said two of its founders sold a 2.25
percent stake in the company, reducing their holding to 54.84
percent.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Ameya Karve in Mumbai at 
 akarve@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
